.Dd March 27, 2026
.Dt SORT 1
.Os Xao
.Sh NAME
.Nm sort
.Nd sort, merge, or sequence check text files
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl u
.Op Ar file ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility conforms to POSIX.1-2024. It reads lines from the specified
.Ar file
operands and writes them to the standard output.
.Pp
If no
.Ar file
operands are specified, or if a
.Ar file
operand is
.Pq Ql - ,
the standard input is read.
.Pp
The following option is supported:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl u
Unique: suppress all but one in each set of lines having equal keys.
If used with sequence checking, verify that the input file contains no
adjacent duplicate lines.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh EXAMPLES
Sort a list of names alphabetically:
.Pp
.Dl $ sort names.txt
.Pp
Sort standard input and remove duplicates:
.Pp
.Dl $ echo "apple\napple\norange" | sort -u
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr comm 1 ,
.Xr join 1 ,
.Xr uniq 1
